]. What is David doing?'

'Well, you know what I think at least [po kraïneï mere],' said Maximov, picking up the historical novel he had been reading when Krug came in. 'But we are not through with you yet, I shall have Anna talk to you, too, whether you like it or not. She may fare better. I believe David is with her in the kitchen garden. We lunch at one.'

